    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Manifolds and Exhaust Gas Recirculation (EGR) - Removal - Exhaust Gas
        Recirculation (EGR) Valve
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Exhaust Gas Recirculation (EGR) Valve</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid serious personal injury or possible death, disconnect the main battery negative terminal
                    before disconnecting or connecting any electrical components.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f3000406.2" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj17/j17006.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>EGR valve retaining bolts</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M6 x 35 (2)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect EGR valve electrical harness.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove two EGR valve retaining bolts (M6 x 35).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000406.3" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ09/J09042.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the EGR valve</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EGR Valve Puller Arm (offset), ZTSE4685</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EGR Valve Puller, ZTSE4669</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EGR Valve</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use the EGR Valve Puller to remove valve. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_74.xml" xrefid="E30004C" appearance="hottext">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>.
                Remove as follows:
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, take extra caution when removing the EGR valve, as there is little
                        clearance between the air inlet elbow nipple and the EGR Valve Puller.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Turn the EGR valve counter-clockwise until it stops.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Position the two support legs over the EGR bolt holes in the intake manifold.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install one arm pin (one supplied with ZTSE4669) under the EGR left side mounting bolt
                    hole. Attach other end to puller beam.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install one arm pin (ZTSE4685, Offset arm) under the EGR right side mounting bolt hole.
                    Attach other end to puller beam.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000407" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ17/J17003.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>EGR valve removed</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn puller shaft thread counter-clockwise to release EGR valve.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, when removing or installing the EGR valve only, make sure to remove
                    loose ash deposits (vacuum) or debris from inside the intake manifold.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard two O-rings and gasket.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
